author: Eric Page
title: Iowa vs. Maryland game time and TV schedule set
text:
Iowa vs. Maryland game time and TV schedule set Posted: The latest news and information on the University of Iowa Hawkeyes sports teams, including football, basketball, volleyball, baseball, softball and more. More >> IOWA CITY (KWWL) - 
The University of Iowa has announced the October 31 game against Maryland will kick-off at 2:30 p.m. and will be broadcast regionally on ABC. 
The Hawkeyes, who are undefeated overall and in the conference, will host the Terrapins at Kinnick Stadium. Iowa is off this week. Maryland, who is winless in the conference and 2-4 overall, faces Penn State this week. 
Today's announcement leaves three of Iowa's five remaining games where kick-off times have not been announced. The only time that has been announced is the 7 p.m. kick-off when Iowa hosts Minnesota on November 14.
